    <tags>tetris game console terminal assembly retro tui</tags>
    <summary>A retro TUI Tetris for the Windows console, hand-written in x86-64 assembly.</summary>
    <description>
Retro Tetris is a Tetris for the Windows console, hand-written in x86-64
assembly (NASM). It renders on a green-phosphor palette with ANSI escape
codes, reads input through the Win32 console API, and links no C runtime.

After install, run `retro-tetris` in a terminal to play. Controls: move 7/9
or arrows, rotate 8/Up, soft drop 4/Down, hard drop Space, pause P, quit
Q/Esc.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/rugbedbugg/Retro-Tetris/releases/tag/v1.0.0</releaseNotes>
